The paper presents a novel adversarial framework for training deep belief networks (DBNs) and includes numerical experiments in computer vision and neurosciences. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves developing a highly parallelizable numerical algorithm, which suggests a possible fit with cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
